      "author": "Kathrin",
      "excerpt": "After driving straight across Sweden for five days, we finally reached Senja, Norway's largest island, often lovingly called \"Little Norway.\" And let me tell you ‚Äì it was love at first sight.\n\nWe'd heard so many wonderful things about the island, but nothing could have prepared us for just how breathtaking it really is. Before crossing the bridge to Senja, we made one last pit stop in Finnsnes, the final proper town before the island.",
      "categories": [
        "üá≥üá¥ Norway",
        "üöê Van life",
        "üåÖ On the road"
      ],
      "heroImage": "/images/van-life/segla-and-hesten/2025-09-09 12.57.19_Segla und Hesten_4096.jpg",
      "heroImageAlt": "View of mount Segla on Senja",
