      "date": "2025-10-19",
      "author": "Kathrin",
      "excerpt": "We spent a few incredible days in Troms√∏, often called the \"Gateway to the Arctic.\" It's the largest city in Northern Norway, and back in the 19th century, a French visitor gave it the nickname \"Paris of the North.\" After spending some time here, we can see why ‚Äì it's lively, stylish, and full of surprises, even this far above the Arctic Circle. \n Our first stop was the Arctic Cathedral (Ishavskatedralen), one of Norway's most distinctive and modern churches. With its striking triangular shape inspired by Arctic icebergs, it's impossible to miss.",
