      "author": "Kathrin",
      "excerpt": "After spending a few days in Troms√∏, we travelled to Sommar√∏y, a tiny fishing village which literally means 'Summer Island' in Norwegian. This tiny fishing village is located about an hour west of Troms√∏ and is home to around 350 people and more seagulls than inhabitants. It boasts some of the most beautiful beaches in Northern Norway.\n\nWe parked Wilma at a private campsite right by the sea. It was surrounded by crystal-clear water and white sand. It was beautiful to look at, and the weather was teasing us to go for a swim - but the water temperature isn't \"pleasant\" ü•∂",
